      • Connect

        @BusMethod
@BusAnnotations(value=@BusAnnotation(name="org.freedesktop.DBus.Method.NoReply",value="true"))
void Connect()
             throws org.alljoyn.bus.BusException
        Tell the onboardee to connect to the Personal AP. The onboardee is recommended to use channel switching feature if it is available.
        Throws:
        org.alljoyn.bus.BusException

      • ConfigureWiFi

        @BusMethod(signature="ssn",
           replySignature="n")
short ConfigureWiFi(java.lang.String ssid,
                            java.lang.String passphrase,
                            short authType)
                    throws org.alljoyn.bus.BusException
        Send the personal AP info to the onboardee. When the authType is equal to "any", the onboardee needs to try out all the possible authentication types it supports to connect to the AP. If authType parameter is invalid then the AllJoyn error code org.alljoyn.Error.OutOfRange will be returned
        Parameters:
        ssid -
        passphrase -
        WPA2_AUTO - = -3, WPA_AUTO = -2, any = -1, Open = 0 , WEP = 1, WPA_TKIP =2, WPA_CCMP = 3, WPA2_TKIP = 4, WPA2_CCMP = 5, WPS = 6
        Throws:
        org.alljoyn.bus.BusException

      • Offboard

        @BusMethod
@BusAnnotations(value=@BusAnnotation(name="org.freedesktop.DBus.Method.NoReply",value="true"))
void Offboard()
              throws org.alljoyn.bus.BusException
        Tell the onboardee to disconnect from the personal AP, clear the personal AP configuration fields, and start the soft AP mode.
        Throws:
        org.alljoyn.bus.BusException

      • GetScanInfo

        @BusMethod(replySignature="qa(sn)")
ScanInfo GetScanInfo()
                     throws org.alljoyn.bus.BusException
        Scan all the WiFi access points in the onboardee's proximity. Some device may not support this feature.
        Throws:
        org.alljoyn.bus.BusException - if feature is unsupported, AllJoyn error code org.alljoyn.Error.FeatureNotAvailable will be returned in the AllJoyn response.
